            </div>
          ))}
        </div>

        <p class="mt-8 text-ink-300 leading-relaxed">The most common workflow failure is disconnecting tracking from optimisation. Teams set up a tracker, look at the dashboard occasionally, but do not have a defined process for converting citation frequency data into content or entity tasks. Establish a standing review meeting or sprint ritual — even monthly — where tracking data is reviewed, anomalies are investigated, and at least one optimisation action is identified and assigned before the meeting ends.</p>
      </section>

      <section id="known-tools">
        <h2 class="anchor-top">Known GEO Tracking Tools and Platforms</h2>
        <p><strong>The GEO tracker market is young and fast-moving — any specific tool list has a limited shelf life, and features, pricing, and platform viability change frequently.</strong> The following represents publicly known platforms and approaches as of mid-2026, provided as a starting point for your own evaluation rather than a definitive or ranked comparison.</p>

        <p class="mt-4 text-ink-300 leading-relaxed">Dedicated GEO and AI visibility tracking platforms that have been publicly active include <strong>Profound</strong> (enterprise-focused, strong on competitive benchmarking), <strong>Peec AI</strong> (multi-platform tracking with query customisation), <strong>Otterly.ai</strong> (focused on brand monitoring across generative platforms), and <strong>Semrush's AI Toolkit</strong> (integrated within the broader Semrush platform for existing users). These are not endorsements — evaluate each against your own requirements using a trial account.</p>

        <p class="mt-4 text-ink-300 leading-relaxed">Established SEO platforms including <strong>Ahrefs</strong>, <strong>Moz</strong>, and <strong>BrightEdge</strong> have released or announced AI visibility features. These are worth assessing if you already use the platform, but verify that the tracking capability is live and functional rather than a roadmap commitment — and that it meets the essential criteria above (scheduled runs, history retention, multi-platform).</p>

        <p class="mt-4 text-ink-300 leading-relaxed">For technically capable teams, a DIY approach using the OpenAI, Perplexity, or Gemini APIs directly — combined with a database for storing results and a BI tool for visualisation — provides maximum flexibility and often lower cost at scale. The trade-off is engineering overhead and ongoing maintenance as platform APIs change.</p>

